5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS RELATED TO HEALTH UTILIZATION REVIEW;
6 REQUIRING A PHYSICIAN LICENSED IN THE STATE TO MAKE OR REVIEW AN ADVERSE
7 DETERMINATION OR REVIEW A GRIEVANCE; AND PROVIDING FOR AUTOMATIC APPROVAL OF A
8 HEALTH CARE SERVICE UNDER REVIEW IF A HEALTH INSURANCE ISSUER OR UTILIZATION REVIEW
9 ORGANIZATION FAILS TO COMPLY WITH REQUIREMENTS.”
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
12
13 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Qualifications of individuals who make or review adverse
14 determinations. (1) Only a physician may make an adverse determination pursuant to 33-32-211 or 33-32-212
15 for a utilization review organization.
16 (2) A physician who makes an adverse determination:
17 (a) must possess a current, valid nonrestricted license to practice medicine under Title 37, chapter
18 3, part 3;
19 (b) must have a specialty that focuses on the diagnosis and treatment of the condition being
20 reviewed; and
21 (c) shall make the adverse determination under the clinical direction of one of the utilization review
22 organization’s medical directors who is responsible for the oversight of the utilization review activities. A
23 medical director used for this purpose must be a physician licensed in the state.
24
25 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Qualifications of individuals who review grievance. (1) Only a
26 physician may review a grievance as provided under 33-32-308 or 33-32-309 for a utilization review
27 organization.
